            "text": "apremilast 30 mg orally twice a day was started. The patient gradually improved, allowing prednisone tapering to a minimal dose of 12.5 mg daily. On February 19, 2020, he was enough stabilized to travel to Milan, Northern Italy, to be evaluated for brain radiotherapy. On February 26, he developed a severe cough with high fever (TC 40\u00b0C) and a chest X-Ray revealed bilateral interstitial pneumonia with positive swab to SARS CoV2. After referral to the Infective Disease Unit, the patient started treatment with Lopinavir/Ritonavir400/100 mg twice a day and intravenous Ceftriaxone 2 g/day. He was discharged on March 3, clinically healed after two consecutive negative SARS-CoV-2 swabs. Apremilast had never been stopped during the COVID-19 hospitalization, with acceptable control of the psoriasis, limited to mild scaling and erythema, especially on the trunk (Fig. 2) .",
